West Nile Virus Transmission In The Middle East
-----------------------------------------------
In the Middle East, it has been suggested that migratory birds [may be
responsible for dissemination of the virus within this region across
Israel, Jordan and possibly Saudi Arabia. {Unfortunately there is little
or no surveillance and/or health education as regards West Nile virus [over
most of this region, despite the real and perceived threats of the virus
in these past few months. In late summer, at the beginning of the school
year (early September), there were newspaper reports of the hunting of
migratory birds in some regions of Saudi Arabia. These birds were said to
have been hunted for eating purposes. This coincided with the time in
neighboring Israel when there was a rise in [West Nile virus-related
disease. [A question that needs to be addressed is whether it may be
possible for West Nile virus to be transmitted directly (perhaps through
virus shed in faecal droppings,etc) to other susceptible animals [in this
region, such as wild equids?
--
Shamsudeen Fagbo, DVM
